JOHANNESBURG - The rand weakened on Friday afternoon after the news that Fitch had downgraded SA s rating to junk status being the second major rating agency to do so this week.READ: Fitch downgrades SA to junk statusS&P Global Ratings downgraded the country s rating to sub-investment grade on Monday.Fitch cut both the foreign currency and local currency ratings by one notch on Friday afternoon on concerns that recent political events including a major cabinet reshuffle would weaken standards of governance and public finances and was likely to result in a change of economic policy direction.The rand weakened to an intraday worst level of R13.8426 to the dollar on the news after hovering around the R13.77$ level for the better part of the day.iNet Bridge